option for washington politicians. </p><blockquote dir="ltr" style="margin-right: 0px"> <p><b>- governor (candidate last) will veto appropriations bills that exceed spending targets.</b> he will veto any non-defense discretionary appropriations bill that grows spending at a rate greater than inflation minus one percent (cpi-1%). this will save $300 billion over 10 years. </p><p><b>- governor (candidate last) will review and reevaluate all federal spending programs.</b> he will undertake an exhaustive review of each federal program to eliminate wasteful programs. </p><p><b>- governor (candidate last) believes the president needs the line-item veto power.</b> giving the president this power would allow us to make tremendous strides in eliminating earmarks and cutting inefficient programs. </p><p><b>- <a href="http://www.(candidate full).com/news/press-releases/restraining_government_spending">click here</a> to read governor (candidate last)'s plan to cut wasteful spending.</b> </p></blockquote> <p><b> <u>building a stronger economy:</u> </b> </p><p><b>governor (candidate last) has outlined a conservative blueprint to strengthen our economy.</b> in addition to lowering taxes on the american people and bringing fiscal responsibility to washington, governor (candidate last)'s economic blueprint includes initiatives to reform the tort system, become energy secure, strengthen our education system and promote trade around the world. </p><blockquote dir="ltr" style="margin-right: 0px"> <p><b>- <a href="http://www.(candidate full).com/news/press-releases/(candidate last)_agenda_10.9.07">click here</a> to read governor (candidate last)'s conservative blueprint to strengthen our economy.</b> </p></blockquote> <p><b> <u>improving america's health care system:</u> </b> </p><p><b>governor (candidate last) will improve our health care system by putting conservative, market-based principles to work.</b> governor (candidate last)'s health care reform plan is a comprehensive solution 